:17:"Princess_Celestia";s:12:"character_id";s:2:"63";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:6:"Shoski";s:4:"text";s:205:"The difference there is that Rarity had a horn which was actually the thing that was directing the magic. Without a horn, there&#039;s not a lot of ways in the show that ponies can actually project magic. ";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1417065362";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#daea0f";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14170653617";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#69d6ef";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1122928;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1122928";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"2";s:7:"user_id";s:5:"10702";s:6:"handle";s:6:"Shoski";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1188";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:17:"Princess_Celestia";s:4:"text";s:295:"Firstly, it&#039;s never implied that it has to be a unicorn, and if it does, these other books might not follow the same rules. Secondly, Shoski has no significant control over it, and should it become necessary, I can make it impossible to physically project, in favor of more passive effects.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1417065650";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#d0c3cc";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14170656555";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#3e51f3";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1122930;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1122930";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:2:"25";s:6:"handle";s:17:"Princess_Celestia";s:12:"character_id";s:2:"63";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:6:"Shoski";s:4:"text";s:370:"The study of black magic, I am not opposed to. The book having negative effects on the pony in contact with it or some passive effects on the environment around it, I am also not opposed to, though we&#039;ll have to talk about it just a bit. But yeah...Earth ponies can&#039;t do magic. There&#039;s some things we could do...but it would be more of a temporary thing. ";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1417065833";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#daea0f";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14170658323";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#69d6ef";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1122938;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1122938";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"2";s:7:"user_id";s:5:"10702";s:6:"handle";s:6:"Shoski";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1188";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:17:"Princess_Celestia";s:4:"text";s:357:"On that topic, it has been shown that pegasuses do utilize some variety of magic, and while once again it&#039;s not completely clear it also implied that earth ponies have some variety as well. The difference may be that only unicorns can cast &lt;i&gt;spells&lt;/i&gt;. I don&#039;t know how much of a difference it makes, but it&#039;s something to note.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1417066111";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#d0c3cc";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14170661162";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#3e51f3";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1122940;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1122940";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:2:"25";s:6:"handle";s:17:"Princess_Celestia";s:12:"character_id";s:2:"63";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:6:"Shoski";s:4:"text";s:581:"You&#039;re right about that. It is heavily implied in the show (and I think mentioned once or twice) that Pegasai and Earth Ponies have magic inside them, but it&#039;s a passive sort of magic. They can&#039;t cast spells, that&#039;s the main thing. A good scenario is this: An Earth Pony has a cursed object which makes them angry but also makes all plants that they interact with grow wild and dark. They don&#039;t do it on purpose, but it is a manipulation of an outside object on their magic. But like...they couldn&#039;t start shooting dark energy or something, you know? ";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1417066334";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#daea0f";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14170663335";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#69d6ef";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1122947;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1122947";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"2"